      <TextArea editable="false" layoutX="10.0" layoutY="53.0" prefHeight="300.0" prefWidth="380.0" text="---[Panels]-----------------------------------------------------------&#10;&#10;The left panel shows the system entities that are available. The add button above the panel can be used to add new system entities. The glasses symbol allows inspection and modification of the selected entity properties. The delete button is used to delete the selected entity.&#10;&#10;The middle panel shows the concrete services that are available for the currently selected system entity, sorted by service registry. A green mark means the system entity workflow uses the service; a red mark means that the service is not used by the system entity workflow. The glasses symbol allows inspection and modification of the selected service description as well as the service profile of each service.&#10;&#10;The right panel shows the definition of the workflow for the currently selected systen entity. Both a graphical representation and a specification with to the ReSeP workflow definition language are available. The save button can be used to save the workflow after changing it in the text area.&#10;&#10;&#10;---[dTAS Configuration bar]----------------------------------------&#10;&#10;The 'Open' button allows the user to open a new system entity or open a different set of available services. Be careful to not run input profiles with entities that use not-imported service registries.  &#10;&#10;The 'Configure' button allows dynamic configuration of the behavior of the underlying ReSeP platform. Message loss and communication delay can be defined, as well as the real time that matches with a logic time unit in the system. This feature is active but currently not used in the predefined scenarios.&#10;&#10;The 'Help' button opens a window with the information you are reading now. &#10;&#10;The 'About' button opens a window with general information about dTAS and a email address to contact the development team." wrapText="true" />
      <TextArea editable="false" layoutX="10.0" layoutY="383.0" prefHeight="300.0" prefWidth="380.0" text="---[Panels]-----------------------------------------------------------&#10;&#10;The left panel shows the input profile that can be used to test the loaded configuration (i.e., system entities with available concrete services). The green triangle buttons on the right hand side are used to run the corresponding input profile (parallel runs are not supported). Clicking the red mark stops the execution of the running input profile. The glasses symbol allows inspection and modification of the selected input profile. The delete button is used to delete the selected input profile.&#10;&#10;The right panel shows graphs and data tables about the results of the input profile. When the execution of the input profile completes, the results will be shown in the graphs and overview tables. &#10;&#10;---[dTAS Experimention bar]----------------------------------------&#10;&#10;The 'Open' button allows opening new input profiles (Open Profile item).&#10;&#10;The 'Save' button allows the user to save the results to a file. &#10;&#10;The progress bar shows the progress of an ongoing execution of an input profile." wrapText="true" />
